      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0622P0-04788'>
        <a name='S5LV0622P0_20010227_GCR_313'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-rachel-gardner' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0622P0_20010227_GCR_313' title='Link to this speech by Ms Rachel Gardner' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-rachel-gardner" title="Ms Rachel Gardner">Baroness Gardner of Parkes</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I find Schedule 6 quite difficult to understand. In particular, it refers to premises excluded from the right to manage. Paragraph 1(1)(b) states that if you have a garage it should be part of the residential premises. Does that mean that that would be enfranchisable with whatever else one was enfranchising?
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0622P0-04789'>
        <a name='S5LV0622P0_20010227_GCR_314'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-monson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
